            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* Requesting $9 billion for NASA's Science Mission Directorate to restore funding stability and maintain U.S. global leadership in space exploration and scientific discovery.\n* Funding supports high-priority, peer-reviewed Decadal Survey missions that advance our understanding of the Solar System, Earth's climate, and the universe.\n* Every $1 invested in NASA returns approximately $3 to the U.S. economy, fueling a high-tech industrial workforce and domestic innovation.\n* Strategic investment ensures the U.S. remains the partner of choice in international space missions and maintains a competitive edge over rapidly expanding foreign space programs.",
